Someone must've changed it then.

270
00:14:53,559 --> 00:14:55,360
What happened?
Did you offend the landlord?

271
00:15:01,640 --> 00:15:04,659
[This place belongs to Yun Ma Group.]
[Please leave in 24 hours.]

272
00:15:06,160 --> 00:15:07,559
Did your landlord text you?

273
00:15:08,079 --> 00:15:09,120
It's nothing.

274
00:15:09,680 --> 00:15:11,280
How did you enter my house last time?

275
00:15:11,720 --> 00:15:12,759
I climbed the wall.

276
00:15:12,920 --> 00:15:13,879
Bring me there.

277
00:15:16,079 --> 00:15:17,079
Wait for me.

278
00:15:22,840 --> 00:15:23,680
It's there.

279
00:15:23,920 --> 00:15:24,720
Where?

280
00:15:38,319 --> 00:15:40,759
Are you a cat? You're so slick.

281
00:15:40,879 --> 00:15:41,720
What did you say?

282
00:15:41,879 --> 00:15:43,280
I told you to be careful.

283
00:15:43,360 --> 00:15:45,280
Everyone is worried about you.

284
00:15:45,720 --> 00:15:46,879
Next time, I won't let them be worried.

285
00:16:09,120 --> 00:16:15,040
♪ My friends wanted me to have a walk ♪

286
00:16:16,439 --> 00:16:22,280
♪ I walked to somewhere unknown ♪

287
00:16:23,800 --> 00:16:28,319
♪ I saw a dog in the corner ♪

288
00:16:28,439 --> 00:16:32,079
♪ Only the dog accompanies me ♪

289
00:16:32,280 --> 00:16:36,639
♪ The dog is by my side ♪

290
00:16:38,639 --> 00:16:43,999
♪ I hate the world and it's ridiculous ♪

291
00:16:45,879 --> 00:16:51,639
♪ Seems like everyone
is laughing at me ♪

292
00:16:53,240 --> 00:16:57,879
♪ They laugh because
the road is not for me ♪

293
00:16:59,240 --> 00:17:00,280
I think...

294
00:17:01,480 --> 00:17:02,800
this isn't the place for me.

295
00:17:24,279 --> 00:17:25,880
I think it's here.

296
00:17:26,760 --> 00:17:30,720
The real astronomy club is
smaller than I expected.

297
00:17:38,520 --> 00:17:39,439
Hello.

298
00:17:40,720 --> 00:17:41,640
Someone is coming!

299
00:17:41,640 --> 00:17:43,159
My goodness! It's a girl as well!

300
00:17:43,279 --> 00:17:44,480
Hello!

301
00:17:44,840 --> 00:17:46,720
Are you here to join the club?

302
00:17:46,919 --> 00:17:48,000
-I'm finding for Li...
-Of course she is!

303
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:50,079
Didn't you see the flyers on her hand?

304
00:17:50,679 --> 00:17:52,199
Do you like astronomy?

305
00:17:52,319 --> 00:17:53,439
It's fine. I'm finding for...

306
00:17:53,600 --> 00:17:55,039
I'm glad that you like it.

307
00:17:55,159 --> 00:17:56,679
We don't have many rules here.

308
00:17:56,799 --> 00:17:59,000
But the entrance exam
is troublesome though.

309
00:17:59,199 --> 00:18:01,600
Here, I have a set of 100 questions.

310
00:18:01,720 --> 00:18:03,679
If you can answer
90% of them correctly,

311
00:18:03,799 --> 00:18:05,520
You can become a member of our club.

312
00:18:06,959 --> 00:18:08,039
Here.

313
00:18:08,360 --> 00:18:09,360
Come here!

314
00:18:10,039 --> 00:18:11,240
It's rare for someone to come.

315
00:18:11,400 --> 00:18:13,520
We must let her be at ease.

316
00:18:13,720 --> 00:18:15,079
How can you ask her to do the exam now?

317
00:18:15,240 --> 00:18:16,880
Aren't you scaring her like that?

318
00:18:17,079 --> 00:18:19,799
You know the 100 questions
are quite tough, right?

319
00:18:19,919 --> 00:18:20,840
What should I do then?

320
00:18:20,959 --> 00:18:22,600
Our boss is very strict.

321
00:18:22,799 --> 00:18:24,000
If she doesn't know anything,

322
00:18:24,159 --> 00:18:25,959
she'll be kicked out anyway.

323
00:18:26,240 --> 00:18:27,199
How about this?

324
00:18:27,400 --> 00:18:29,880
We'll guide her through the exam.

325
00:18:31,079 --> 00:18:31,720
That's the only way.

326
00:18:31,840 --> 00:18:33,000
Do you have a pen?

327
00:18:34,079 --> 00:18:35,679
-Pen?
-Are you doing it?

328
00:18:35,799 --> 00:18:36,600
Yeah.

329
00:18:39,679 --> 00:18:40,520
Here.

330
00:18:44,360 --> 00:18:48,360
Did you notice that her eyes
are glowing when she's writing?

331
00:18:48,559 --> 00:18:50,120
She's just like Li Ming Cheng.

332
00:18:50,279 --> 00:18:51,520
I wonder what course is she taking?

333
00:18:53,079 --> 00:18:54,000
Senior Ran Yu?

334
00:18:54,120 --> 00:18:54,760
-Senior.
-You're here?

335
00:18:54,840 --> 00:18:55,640
Nice to meet you.

336
00:18:55,640 --> 00:18:56,880
I'm here to hand in the paper.

337
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:59,600
The questions are too hard.
I didn't finish them.

338
00:18:59,760 --> 00:19:00,640
Sorry for that.

339
00:19:00,720 --> 00:19:01,520
Never mind.

340
00:19:01,640 --> 00:19:03,120
The questions are too hard.

341
00:19:03,240 --> 00:19:05,079
Even the astronomy majors
can't finish them.

342
00:19:05,279 --> 00:19:07,480
Senior, it's normal
if you can't finish them.

343
00:19:08,159 --> 00:19:09,880
I'm relieved then.

344
00:19:10,039 --> 00:19:11,640
I thought I was too stupid for this.

345
00:19:11,760 --> 00:19:13,039
Senior, that's not the case.

346
00:19:13,240 --> 00:19:15,919
You are Kwang Hua University's icon.

347
00:19:16,039 --> 00:19:19,199
Even if our university's icon
can't finish the questions,

348
00:19:19,319 --> 00:19:21,480
I know you still have
some common sense in you.

349
00:19:21,959 --> 00:19:22,480
Please sit.

350
00:19:22,559 --> 00:19:23,520
-Senior, come here.
-I'll have a look.

351
00:19:23,520 --> 00:19:25,159
Please sit down.

352
00:19:32,760 --> 00:19:34,799
Senior, you...

353
00:19:34,959 --> 00:19:35,880
What's wrong?

354
00:19:36,120 --> 00:19:37,039
It's nothing.

355
00:19:37,159 --> 00:19:38,400
The questions are too hard for you.

356
00:19:38,520 --> 00:19:40,120
Senior, I'll ask you
some simple questions.

357
00:19:40,240 --> 00:19:42,279
How many planets
do our solar system have?

358
00:19:42,439 --> 00:19:44,520
Of course I know.
There are nine planets.

359
00:19:44,640 --> 00:19:46,919
We have Venus, Jupiter, Saturn, Mars,

360
00:19:47,039 --> 00:19:50,439
Mercury, Earth, Neptune and Pluto.

361
00:19:50,600 --> 00:19:52,480
My guardian planet is Pluto too.

362
00:19:53,360 --> 00:19:55,760
What's the brightest star?

363
00:19:55,959 --> 00:19:57,319
It's the Polaris.

364
00:19:57,840 --> 00:20:01,319
In the Book of Songs, which planet
does the phrase July's fire refers to?

365
00:20:01,439 --> 00:20:02,520
It's Mars.

366
00:20:04,279 --> 00:20:07,600
What does Cassiopeia means then?

367
00:20:07,799 --> 00:20:09,520
They're the fans of TVXQ.

368
00:20:13,840 --> 00:20:15,319
Did you laugh at me just now?

369
00:20:16,279 --> 00:20:17,600
Am I wrong?

370
00:20:17,799 --> 00:20:18,840
What's so funny?

371
00:20:18,959 --> 00:20:20,360
You are wrong in many ways.

372
00:20:20,880 --> 00:20:26,679
In 2006, the IAU has classified Pluto
as a dwarf planet.

373
00:20:26,880 --> 00:20:28,480
It's not a planet anymore.

374
00:20:28,640 --> 00:20:30,799
Now, our solar system
only has eight planets left.

375
00:20:30,959 --> 00:20:32,279
Not nine.

376
00:20:32,520 --> 00:20:35,919
The brightest star is called Sirius.

377
00:20:36,120 --> 00:20:37,079
Sirius.

378
00:20:37,199 --> 00:20:41,559
The Polaris is only the 47th
brightest star in the world.

379
00:20:41,799 --> 00:20:45,959
The phrase July's fire
refers to the α Sco,

380
00:20:46,240 --> 00:20:48,919
or also known as Alpha Scopii.

381
00:20:49,199 --> 00:20:50,400
It's not referring to Mars.

382
00:20:50,720 --> 00:20:53,959
For the last question,
it's about common sense.

383
00:20:54,199 --> 00:20:55,880
I guess you're correct then.

384
00:21:01,600 --> 00:21:03,120
Kwang Hua University's icon,

385
00:21:03,240 --> 00:21:04,840
the famous and talented lady,

386
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:07,360
I didn't expect that you would
be a barred spiral galaxy.

387
00:21:07,959 --> 00:21:09,079
I learned something new today.

388
00:21:09,360 --> 00:21:12,439
Where can I find Li Ming Cheng
besides this place?

389
00:21:12,559 --> 00:21:13,919
Maybe at the Go club.

390
00:21:14,480 --> 00:21:17,400
You're not here to join our club?

391
00:21:21,279 --> 00:21:22,559
What's going on?

392
00:21:23,199 --> 00:21:26,159
What did she mean by that?
The galaxy thing?

393
00:21:26,439 --> 00:21:28,799
Barred spiral galaxy
is a spiral galaxy...

394
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:31,120
with a central bar-shaped
structure composed of stars.

395
00:21:31,840 --> 00:21:32,760
And,

396
00:21:32,919 --> 00:21:34,640
according to Hubber's classification,

397
00:21:34,760 --> 00:21:38,000
the symbol is SB.

398
00:21:42,279 --> 00:21:43,760
I'm going to kill her!

399
00:21:54,039 --> 00:21:58,279
Which guy will want to marry a girl
with huge debts like you?

400
00:21:58,400 --> 00:22:00,159
If the guy does appear in the future,

401
00:22:00,279 --> 00:22:01,400
remember to tell me.

402
00:22:01,520 --> 00:22:03,159
I'll be the first to give red packets.

403
00:22:09,079 --> 00:22:10,039
You scared me to death!

404
00:22:10,159 --> 00:22:12,279
Why are you so sneaky?

405
00:22:12,520 --> 00:22:13,600
Shi Shi.

406
00:22:16,439 --> 00:22:17,720
Are you finding for me?

407
00:22:18,760 --> 00:22:19,760
It's nothing.

408
00:22:19,880 --> 00:22:21,480
I'm just here to visit you.

409
00:22:21,720 --> 00:22:24,799
Stop pretending. You would've
come in if you wanted to.

410
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:28,000
You waited at the door
for 10 minutes today.

411
00:22:28,159 --> 00:22:29,919
You must be in some trouble.

412
00:22:30,199 --> 00:22:32,240
Tell me what's wrong.

413
00:22:44,039 --> 00:22:44,919
Take this.

414
00:22:45,400 --> 00:22:47,439
I'm sure the college is
pressing you for the fees now.

415
00:22:47,640 --> 00:22:48,760
And it's the end of the month too.

416
00:22:48,880 --> 00:22:49,720
I'm sure you're poor now.

417
00:22:49,799 --> 00:22:51,199
I don't have much inside.

418
00:22:51,279 --> 00:22:52,919
But it's enough for you to get by.

419
00:22:53,799 --> 00:22:55,679
No! I can't take your money!

420
00:22:55,840 --> 00:22:56,600
No!

421
00:22:56,679 --> 00:22:58,319
The money is not under my name anyway.

422
00:22:58,480 --> 00:22:59,679
Why are you rejecting my help?

423
00:23:00,199 --> 00:23:02,240
If I can't help you with this,

424
00:23:02,919 --> 00:23:04,319
how can I still be your brother?

425
00:23:06,240 --> 00:23:07,199
I don't want your help!

426
00:23:08,079 --> 00:23:09,120
Shi Shi.

427
00:23:10,679 --> 00:23:11,919
What's wrong with her?

428
00:23:19,520 --> 00:23:22,159
Did a stranger just glare at me?

429
00:23:22,319 --> 00:23:23,279
Zhou Shi!

430
00:23:24,760 --> 00:23:27,079
What's wrong with you?
Did Li Ming Cheng say anything to you?

431
00:23:27,199 --> 00:23:28,319
I'm fine.

432
00:23:28,559 --> 00:23:31,039
I just thought of something else.

433
00:23:33,360 --> 00:23:35,240
It's this late already?
I haven't bought groceries yet.

434
00:23:35,360 --> 00:23:36,400
What do you guys want to eat?

435
00:23:36,559 --> 00:23:37,319
Hot pot.

436
00:23:37,439 --> 00:23:39,199
Wait. Why are we talking about this?

437
00:23:39,319 --> 00:23:41,360
Szechuan style or Cantonese style?
Spicy or mild?

438
00:23:41,559 --> 00:23:43,279
Spicy, with some peppercorns.

439
00:23:43,480 --> 00:23:44,520
Okay, I'll buy them now.

440
00:23:44,640 --> 00:23:45,640
You go home first.

441
00:23:49,720 --> 00:23:51,559
Wait, there's something
else I need to say.

442
00:23:52,919 --> 00:23:54,279
She distracted me again.

443
00:24:00,279 --> 00:24:01,400
Someone won?

444
00:24:02,400 --> 00:24:05,279
I only left for a short while.

445
00:24:07,159 --> 00:24:09,240
Who's the winner then?

446
00:24:18,480 --> 00:24:19,840
Zhou Shi! Stop running!

447
00:24:32,959 --> 00:24:34,000
She's just like her dad.

448
00:24:34,120 --> 00:24:35,439
She's too fast.

449
00:24:35,679 --> 00:24:36,520
Here!

450
00:24:50,919 --> 00:24:52,159
Ning Fei?

451
00:24:53,439 --> 00:24:54,840
Why are you here?

452
00:24:55,720 --> 00:24:57,319
Did you run away from home?

453
00:24:58,159 --> 00:25:00,959
But wait, you're staying alone, right?

454
00:25:01,679 --> 00:25:03,880
You got chased out by the landlord?

455
00:25:05,640 --> 00:25:07,640
-It's none of your business.
-Where are you going?

456
00:25:07,880 --> 00:25:09,959
The park? Or the bridge pier?

457
00:25:10,279 --> 00:25:11,840
Is there any decent place for you?

458
00:25:12,319 --> 00:25:13,319
I'm sure you can't find one.

459
00:25:13,559 --> 00:25:14,840
If I didn't find you,

460
00:25:14,959 --> 00:25:16,959
will you just stay here for the night?

461
00:25:19,400 --> 00:25:20,880
How long have you been squatting here?

462
00:25:21,039 --> 00:25:22,199
Have you eaten?

463
00:25:22,640 --> 00:25:23,799
I have.

464
00:25:28,880 --> 00:25:29,840
Follow me.

465
00:25:29,959 --> 00:25:30,959
Where are we going?

466
00:25:31,079 --> 00:25:33,039
Of course we're going home.

467
00:25:33,159 --> 00:25:34,720
Let's eat first.

468
00:26:00,480 --> 00:26:02,720
I think the mushroom is cooked.
I'll have one.

469
00:26:02,959 --> 00:26:04,120
I want beef.

470
00:26:04,799 --> 00:26:06,039
I'll take the shrimp paste.

471
00:26:08,279 --> 00:26:10,199
Who told you guys to eat?
Put down your chopsticks!

472
00:26:10,520 --> 00:26:12,000
Aren't you guys
explaining anything to me?

473
00:26:12,079 --> 00:26:14,559
There's an extra person in the house.
What's going on here?

474
00:26:14,760 --> 00:26:17,319
How can he just blend in like that?

475
00:26:17,319 --> 00:26:18,880
This is ridiculous!

476
00:26:19,959 --> 00:26:21,199
You. Who asked you to eat?

477
00:26:21,319 --> 00:26:22,319
Put down your chopsticks!

478
00:26:24,520 --> 00:26:25,959
You dare to take my beef?

479
00:26:26,600 --> 00:26:27,520
You!

480
00:26:27,679 --> 00:26:28,760
Okay, calm down.

481
00:26:28,959 --> 00:26:30,319
I brought him back.

482
00:26:30,439 --> 00:26:31,760
Just scold me if you want to.

483
00:26:32,039 --> 00:26:34,000
Why are you angry at a kid?

484
00:26:34,159 --> 00:26:36,000
Yeah, I was preparing to scold you.

485
00:26:36,159 --> 00:26:37,439
It's fine if you bring him home.

486
00:26:37,559 --> 00:26:38,679
But what's with his luggage?

487
00:26:38,799 --> 00:26:40,319
Is he staying in our house?

488
00:26:40,720 --> 00:26:42,400
If the lock is broken,
find someone to fix it.

489
00:26:42,520 --> 00:26:44,480
Why are you staying
in your neighbour's house?

490
00:26:46,120 --> 00:26:47,720
It's not that simple.

491
00:26:48,000 --> 00:26:49,679
He was evicted from his place.

492
00:26:49,799 --> 00:26:51,520
And Madam He is
on a business trip right now.

493
00:26:51,679 --> 00:26:54,799
Just let him stay here for tonight.
If not, he'll sleep in the streets.

494
00:26:55,279 --> 00:26:57,159
He can stay in a hotel, right?

495
00:26:57,400 --> 00:26:58,400
The madam is so generous.

496
00:26:58,400 --> 00:27:00,120
I'm sure he has a lot of pocket money.

497
00:27:00,600 --> 00:27:03,159
She gave us 10,000 yuan per month
to take care of him, right?

498
00:27:04,199 --> 00:27:06,360
10,000 yuan? What do you mean?

499
00:27:06,600 --> 00:27:07,520
Fei Fei.

500
00:27:07,679 --> 00:27:09,840
Are you taking care of Ning Fei
since you took her money?

501
00:27:10,880 --> 00:27:12,559
If you send him back,

502
00:27:12,679 --> 00:27:14,400
you won't get any money.

503
00:27:15,679 --> 00:27:16,919
How much did you take from her?

504
00:27:17,319 --> 00:27:19,720
It's not much. It's around 30,000 yuan.

505
00:27:20,199 --> 00:27:21,919
You're quite daring, huh?

506
00:27:22,360 --> 00:27:24,199
How much do you have left?

507
00:27:24,640 --> 00:27:25,520
There's nothing left.

508
00:27:25,679 --> 00:27:26,840
What?

509
00:27:27,679 --> 00:27:28,959
Actually, there's some money left.

510
00:27:29,199 --> 00:27:34,600
But I have nothing left after I bought
some clothes and a branded bag.

511
00:27:34,919 --> 00:27:36,480
30,000 yuan?

512
00:27:36,720 --> 00:27:38,799
We can pay our rent for
half a year with that money.

513
00:27:38,959 --> 00:27:40,760
And you just spent it like that?

514
00:27:41,079 --> 00:27:42,039
Fine.

515
00:27:42,199 --> 00:27:43,880
Just let him stay here then.

516
00:27:44,079 --> 00:27:45,559
But where can he sleep?

517
00:27:53,439 --> 00:27:54,520
You're really capable.

518
00:27:54,640 --> 00:27:56,880
You took the curtain from my wardrobe.

519
00:27:57,720 --> 00:27:59,159
We should not waste resources, right?

520
00:27:59,360 --> 00:28:01,159
With this, the living room
can be cut off.

521
00:28:01,279 --> 00:28:03,199
And he can stay here then.

522
00:28:03,400 --> 00:28:04,840
You're right.

523
00:28:05,039 --> 00:28:05,959
Slowly.

524
00:28:07,880 --> 00:28:08,840
Done.

525
00:28:10,959 --> 00:28:12,240
I'm fine.

526
00:28:15,919 --> 00:28:17,279
How is it, Xiao Fei?

527
00:28:17,559 --> 00:28:19,799
This sofa can be your bed.

528
00:28:20,000 --> 00:28:21,240
If you want to sleep at night,

529
00:28:21,319 --> 00:28:23,640
just pull the curtains.

530
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:25,919
I'll get you some blankets later.

531
00:28:26,039 --> 00:28:27,360
You just sleep here for tonight.

532
00:28:31,079 --> 00:28:33,959
I'm doing things for him
yet he has the nerves to sleep now?

533
00:28:34,799 --> 00:28:36,199
He's been outside for the entire day.

534
00:28:36,319 --> 00:28:38,039
Just let him sleep.

535
00:28:42,079 --> 00:28:43,439
Look at him.

536
00:28:43,559 --> 00:28:46,039
He looks like the cat that comes
to our house occasionally, right?

537
00:28:47,039 --> 00:28:49,840
You mean the cat
that does this to me?

538
00:28:52,360 --> 00:28:53,720
Yeah, he looks like it.

539
00:28:54,120 --> 00:28:56,799
The cat doesn't want to
be friendly to me even if I fed it.

540
00:28:57,199 --> 00:28:59,760
He's closer to you than anyone else.

541
00:28:59,959 --> 00:29:02,480
I'll not interrupt you guys then.

542
00:29:02,600 --> 00:29:03,679
What are you talking about?

543
00:29:06,400 --> 00:29:08,893
[Mother]

544
00:29:11,959 --> 00:29:13,679
He's just like a cat.

545
00:29:21,480 --> 00:29:22,360
Mum?

546
00:29:23,640 --> 00:29:25,640
I'm fine. How are you?

547
00:29:26,959 --> 00:29:28,400
Dad, he's...

548
00:29:30,520 --> 00:29:32,919
Don't worry, I'll settle the money.

549
00:29:33,079 --> 00:29:34,240
I got the scholarship recently.

550
00:29:34,360 --> 00:29:35,760
I'll send them home tomorrow.

551
00:29:36,079 --> 00:29:37,919
Just use them first.

552
00:29:38,959 --> 00:29:40,959
I'm really fine. Don't worry, mum.

553
00:29:41,319 --> 00:29:42,480
Goodbye, mum.

554
00:30:11,319 --> 00:30:12,319
Oh no.

555
00:30:12,720 --> 00:30:14,159
Even with the scholarship,

556
00:30:14,319 --> 00:30:16,880
I can only last until next month.

557
00:30:17,640 --> 00:30:20,799
And I need to send some money back too.

558
00:30:21,319 --> 00:30:23,199
And I'm not working too.

559
00:30:23,559 --> 00:30:26,760
My goodness! This is frustrating!

560
00:30:27,520 --> 00:30:31,360
I thought I could give back
Wei Qing his interests.

561
00:30:31,600 --> 00:30:33,079
But now,

562
00:30:33,520 --> 00:30:36,559
I think this is just
my wishful thinking.

563
00:30:40,360 --> 00:30:42,439
The door is not locked.

564
00:30:44,919 --> 00:30:46,079
What's wrong?

565
00:30:47,079 --> 00:30:48,079
I'm hungry.

566
00:30:50,559 --> 00:30:52,159
The noodle's here!

567
00:30:54,199 --> 00:30:56,480
You ate a lot just now.

568
00:30:56,640 --> 00:30:58,240
Why are you hungry already?

569
00:30:58,360 --> 00:30:59,679
Aren't you hungry?

570
00:31:01,120 --> 00:31:03,600
Now that you say it,
I'm quite hungry now.

571
00:31:03,760 --> 00:31:05,400
You didn't eat much just now.

572
00:31:05,640 --> 00:31:06,919
How did you know?

573
00:31:08,240 --> 00:31:09,439
I was looking at you.

574
00:31:09,600 --> 00:31:11,520
Why are you thinking so much?

575
00:31:11,640 --> 00:31:13,000
You even count the amount you could eat.

576
00:31:13,120 --> 00:31:14,079
Aren't you tired?

577
00:31:15,679 --> 00:31:18,120
If you don't eat, you'll get nightmares.

578
00:31:20,400 --> 00:31:22,199
You're so smart.

579
00:31:26,880 --> 00:31:28,640
I want that egg.

580
00:31:37,720 --> 00:31:38,840
Hey.

581
00:31:39,159 --> 00:31:41,199
I don't like my surroundings
to be quiet when I eat.

582
00:31:41,360 --> 00:31:42,880
Can you make some sounds?

583
00:31:48,799 --> 00:31:50,439
I don't mean that.

584
00:31:51,439 --> 00:31:52,640
Never mind.

585
00:31:54,319 --> 00:31:55,799
How about this?

586
00:31:56,319 --> 00:31:59,559
I'll speak and you'll listen.

587
00:31:59,760 --> 00:32:01,480
You can forget everything after this.

588
00:32:01,679 --> 00:32:04,679
Don't take it to your heart, okay?

589
00:32:09,439 --> 00:32:12,319
My dad owes a lot of debts.

590
00:32:12,679 --> 00:32:14,679
I was eleven when that happened.

591
00:32:15,240 --> 00:32:17,679
Every day, someone will come
and demand their payments.

592
00:32:18,360 --> 00:32:20,199
My mum would hug me
and cry when that happened.

593
00:32:20,880 --> 00:32:23,199
After that, we started
to avoid the debtors.

594
00:32:23,319 --> 00:32:24,720
And we came to Ninghai County.

595
00:32:25,000 --> 00:32:27,799
After that, I don't believe
in free lunches anymore.

596
00:32:29,039 --> 00:32:30,880
And I hated to owe people things.

597
00:32:31,720 --> 00:32:33,120
But what I hated the most is...

598
00:32:33,360 --> 00:32:36,000
involving my family in troubles
because of my own mistakes.

599
00:32:37,360 --> 00:32:41,439
But now, I committed
some serious mistakes.

600
00:32:43,360 --> 00:32:46,199
Now I have more debts than my dad.

601
00:32:46,480 --> 00:32:48,520
I think I couldn't
repay them in this life.

602
00:32:50,159 --> 00:32:51,480
Unless...

603
00:32:53,039 --> 00:32:55,240
I were to give something up.

604
00:32:56,039 --> 00:32:56,760
Should I...

605
00:32:56,880 --> 00:32:57,840
No.

606
00:32:59,360 --> 00:33:00,640
Don't agree to that.

607
00:33:03,120 --> 00:33:04,640
I think the same way.

608
00:33:06,880 --> 00:33:09,039
That's enough for today.
I spoke too much.

609
00:33:09,720 --> 00:33:11,000
I'll go to sleep first.

610
00:33:11,799 --> 00:33:13,039
Just forget everything.

611
00:35:07,519 --> 00:35:08,600
Should we wait longer?

612
00:35:08,719 --> 00:35:09,999
Maybe she'll be here.

613
00:35:10,239 --> 00:35:11,640
She doesn't know her situation.

614
00:35:11,799 --> 00:35:13,479
She can only blame herself
if she loses this chance.

615
00:35:13,719 --> 00:35:15,680
I'm here!

616
00:35:16,200 --> 00:35:18,640
I was caught in a traffic jam!
I'm sorry!

617
00:35:20,120 --> 00:35:21,120
It's too late.

618
00:35:23,039 --> 00:35:24,799
I reached here just in time, right?

619
00:35:24,920 --> 00:35:26,600
You are late in my heart.

620
00:35:26,759 --> 00:35:27,920
I have a meeting later.

621
00:35:28,079 --> 00:35:29,160
Wait.

622
00:35:29,840 --> 00:35:31,239
I promise you this.

623
00:35:32,799 --> 00:35:34,440
Before I repay all my debts,

624
00:35:34,640 --> 00:35:35,999
I will stay by your side.

625
00:35:36,200 --> 00:35:38,239
You will follow my every order.

626
00:35:39,160 --> 00:35:40,160
Fine.

627
00:35:40,360 --> 00:35:42,360
You must stay within my 10 metre radius.

628
00:35:42,640 --> 00:35:43,559
Fine!

629
00:35:44,479 --> 00:35:45,440
Deal.

630
00:35:54,960 --> 00:35:56,239
What are you doing?

631
00:35:56,680 --> 00:35:57,880
I'm helping you to get used to this.

632
00:35:58,039 --> 00:36:00,200
You will encounter this in the future.

633
00:36:00,479 --> 00:36:03,319
But don't worry, I won't
do anything too much.

634
00:36:04,759 --> 00:36:07,279
Are you really signing
the contract with me?

635
00:36:08,039 --> 00:36:10,799
You will give me the money, right?

636
00:36:13,920 --> 00:36:17,360
Go and make a card at the counter.
You will need it in the future.

637
00:36:22,519 --> 00:36:23,960
What card?

638
00:36:25,799 --> 00:36:28,360
This is your temporary
authorization card. Please take it.

639
00:36:31,840 --> 00:36:34,039
Can I retake the picture?

640
00:36:34,200 --> 00:36:35,719
Please follow the instructions.

641
00:36:35,840 --> 00:36:37,400
And take the chairman's lift.

642
00:36:37,600 --> 00:36:39,120
Have a pleasant day.

643
00:36:39,279 --> 00:36:40,440
Please follow me.

644
00:36:41,360 --> 00:36:42,880
I take it as a no then.

645
00:36:43,200 --> 00:36:44,840
Miss Zhou, please follow me.

646
00:37:01,585 --> 00:37:04,872
[Is she his girlfriend?]

647
00:37:11,999 --> 00:37:12,999
Hello, Assistant An.

648
00:37:13,200 --> 00:37:14,319
Follow me.

649
00:37:29,680 --> 00:37:32,319
I think I came to somewhere unexpected.

650
00:37:32,600 --> 00:37:35,719
What now? Should I turn back?

651
00:37:35,960 --> 00:37:37,120
Miss Zhou.

652
00:37:37,440 --> 00:37:38,999
The chairman is waiting for you.

653
00:37:43,200 --> 00:37:44,239
Let's go.

654
00:37:55,160 --> 00:37:57,239
Why are you standing there?
Do I need to invite you here?

655
00:38:08,799 --> 00:38:11,640
Celebrities' Charity Night?

656
00:38:13,759 --> 00:38:17,479
It's the famous charity night with
many celebrities attending it, right?

657
00:38:19,079 --> 00:38:21,519
What has this got to do with me?

658
00:38:29,880 --> 00:38:34,160
You are cordially invited alongside
with your partner.

659
00:38:34,719 --> 00:38:35,880
Partner?

660
00:38:36,120 --> 00:38:37,200
Do you understand?

661
00:38:38,799 --> 00:38:42,120
Am I your partner for this?

662
00:38:42,559 --> 00:38:43,999
The charity night will start tomorrow.

663
00:38:44,160 --> 00:38:45,440
Come to the office by afternoon.

664
00:38:45,600 --> 00:38:47,440
No, I can't handle this.

665
00:38:47,559 --> 00:38:48,559
Please find someone else.

666
00:38:48,680 --> 00:38:49,880
Why do I need you then?

667
00:38:50,519 --> 00:38:53,079
I thought I was here as an office girl.

668
00:38:53,239 --> 00:38:54,479
I can make some tea for you.

669
00:38:54,600 --> 00:38:56,160
But this event is too high-class for me.

670
00:38:56,239 --> 00:38:57,120
I can't handle it.

671
00:38:57,239 --> 00:38:58,360
Of course you can't handle it.

672
00:38:58,479 --> 00:39:02,479
It's impossible for you
to be a lady in one day.

673
00:39:02,799 --> 00:39:05,640
You are too much.

674
00:39:05,840 --> 00:39:08,039
But with my help,

675
00:39:08,279 --> 00:39:10,640
although you can't be a lady in one day,

676
00:39:10,799 --> 00:39:13,799
I can still turn you into a vase.

677
00:39:14,360 --> 00:39:17,079
You don't lack them here, don't you?

678
00:39:17,400 --> 00:39:18,759
